  "texts": [
    "The only exception from this rule applies to the norms of the L p spaces and of their powers, which we often denote by ∥ • ∥ p, for 1 ≤ p ≤ ∞.",
    "As usual, for Banach spaces X and Y that are contained in the same topological vector space, we introduce the linear space X ∩ Y which becomes a Banach space when endowed with its natural norm ∥u∥ X∩Y:= ∥u∥ X + ∥u∥ Y, for u ∈ X ∩ Y.",
    "Moreover, we introduce the spacesH:= L 2 (Ω), V:= H 1 (Ω), W:= {v ∈ H 2 (Ω): ∂ n v = 0 on Γ}.",
    "(2.1)Furthermore, by ( •, •), ∥ • ∥, and ⟨•, •⟩, we denote the standard inner product and related norm in H, as well as the dual product between V and its dual V *.",
    "We then have the dense and compact embeddings V ⊂ H ⊂ V *, with the standard identification ⟨v, w⟩ = (v, w) for v ∈ H and w ∈ V.Throughout the paper, we make repeated use of Hölder's inequality, of the elementary Young's inequalityab ≤ δ|a| 2 + 1 4δ |b| 2 ∀ a, b ∈ R, ∀ δ > 0,(2.2)as well as of the continuity of the embeddings H 1 (Ω) ⊂ L p (Ω) for 1 ≤ p ≤ 6 and H 2 (Ω) ⊂ C 0 (Ω)."
  ]
